text.tspan: If you do three jumps in a row without slowing
down, your third jump will be extra high!
Hold down or S to crouch. If you try to jump
while crouching, you'll do a long jump!
Long jumping can help you travel faster
and get over large gaps in tight areas.
If you lean against a wall in mid-air and
press up or W, you'll perform a wall jump!
Leaning against a wall while falling
downwards will let you wall slide, where
you'll fall at a slower velocity than normal.
